                        material force of gravity
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <cb n="left"/><seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_fig24"></figure></seg>
                        <cb n="right"/>
                        Function modified in terms of reception: The beholder's 
                        eye steers to the place 
                        in the pasture where the 
                        grass grows thickest, 
                        no. 1, compares that 
                        with no. 2, and compares 
                        that with no. 3, no. 4, 
                        and no. 5. Base above.
                    </p>
                <pb/> 
                    <p> Third example</p>
                    <p>
                        <cb n="left"/><seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_fig25" type="explanation"></figure></seg>
                        <cb n="right"/>
                        Formal statement: Formation: stable <seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureK"></figure></seg>
                        Functions: Arrangement: vertical <seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureL"></figure></seg>
                        Articulation: rigid <seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureM"></figure></seg>
                        Development:<seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureN"></figure></seg>
                        progressive
                        increase and 
                        progressive decrease
                        Direction of increase: <seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureO"></figure></seg>
                        from top to middle 
                        and from bottom to 
                        middle
                        (Direction of decrease:<seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureP"></figure></seg>
                        from the middle 
                        upwards and from
                        the middle down)
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <cb n="right"/>
                        Conceptual statement:  combination of the 
                        materialistic and the 
                        idealistic conceptions.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <cb n="center"/><seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureQ"></figure></seg>ideal
                        <cb n="right"/><seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_figureR"></figure></seg>material
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        <cb n="left"/><seg><figure xml:id="lesson7_fig26"></figure></seg>
